				 NEWS
				 ====

* The complex executable is gone, all the work is done by the normal
  (a.k.a real) executable. The type of the wavefunctions is selected
  automatically according to the input file.

* Calculation of dynamical polarizabities using linear response
  theory.

* Basic support for full potential all electron species.

* The texinfo documentation has been obsoleted and replaced by an
  online wiki based documentation. The Octopus manual is now located
  at http://www.tddft.org/programs/octopus/wiki/index.php/Manual.
  After installation, there is also a PDF version of the manual at
  <sharedir>/doc/octopus/octopus.pdf.

* Debian packages are generated using the gfortran compiler.
